 Port Elizabeth - SAPS Kabega Park detectives on Tuesday appealed to the public for assistance as they are urgently trying to trace the mother of a three-week-old baby boy, whose body was found in a bushy area near Mission Road opposite the Afrimat Quarry. According to police information, the baby was found covered with a blue baby blanket and a bag of nappies near him. "Police have opened an inquest and anyone who can assist in identifying him or locating his mother is asked to contact D/W/O Bertus Blom at SAPS Kabega on 041-3976833," said police spokesperson, Capt Johan Rheeder. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 